HEADWORD: Mimetite
<hw>Mim"e*tite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ an
imitator. So called because it resembles pyromorphite.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral occurring in pale yellow or brownish
hexagonal crystals. It is an arseniate of lead.</def>⟦br⟧
